article.headline: N. Dakota St. 81, W. Illinois 64
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Ben Woodside had 26 points and seven assists to lead North Dakota State to an 81-64 win over Western Illinois Saturday in a battle of Summit League leaders. NDSU (10-5, 5-1) took a 38-26 lead at half and never trailed again in handing the Leathernecks (6-10, 3-2) their second straight loss. Western Illinois began the week in first place in the Summit League. The Bison shot 55 percent from the field and 50 percent (9-for-18) from 3-point range. They outrebounded Western Illinois 33-25. Mike Nelson and Brett Winkelman had 13 points apiece for NDSU. David Dubois had 24 points and Josh Rivers 16 for the Leathernecks, who went 9-for-9 from the free throw line.
